text: Anyone here help me out with setting up a CTI integration?

Hey eveyone. I'm completely new to HubSpot and this project landed in my arms.
The company already has the webiste with the pages done and they want only to add another page which I have built for them for the app (not the website) using react.
I made the configuration and used the react boilerplate... already finished it, but then I'm getting this error on console when saving the project.
```<e> [HubSpotAutoUploadPlugin] Uploading cms-react-boilerplate/main.js failed
<e> [HubSpotAutoUploadPlugin] Error validating template.
<e> [HubSpotAutoUploadPlugin] line 23611: Error parsing 'js: String, css: String, vendor: String, browser: String': syntax error at position 14, encountered ':', expected '}'
<e> [HubSpotAutoUploadPlugin] line 0: Coded files must be smaller than 1.5 MiB ```
I would appreciate if someone help me with this. Thank you so much.
